Dialog Mode is an Emacs major mode for creating and editing Dialog
files.  The following features are implemented:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Syntax-highlighting.
@item
Indentation.
@item
Motion around and selection of rule definitions.
@item
Align support for alignment of syntax following a rule-head.
@item
Imenu support for topics and rule-heads.
@item
Outline support for comments, rule-heads, and topics.
@item
Comint support for running the Dialog debugger.
@item
Flymake support.
@item
Xref support.
@end itemize
